# Root .dockerignore — applies to the repo-root build context.
# The frontend image builds with context = repo root (see frontend/Dockerfile),
# so without this file `COPY frontend/ ./` drags host node_modules (built for the
# host OS/arch) into the linux image, clobbering the deps stage and breaking vite.
# (backend/ has its own .dockerignore because its context is ./backend.)

# Dependencies — must be reinstalled inside the image for the target platform
**/node_modules

# Build output / caches
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/coverage
**/.vite
**/.turbo
*.tsbuildinfo

# Env & secrets — never bake into an image
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# VCS & OS cruft
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
**/*.log

# Editors
.vscode
.idea
**/*.swp

# Infra / meta not needed in app images
infra
docs
Makefile
TEST.md
